p: Yang et al. [ 87] reported the isolation of eremophilane sesquiterpenes from the Aquilaria sinensis (Lour.) Glig and elucidated their structures by the spectroscopic procedures. Isolated compounds were found out to be 7-β- H-9-(10)-ene-11,12-epoxy-8-oxoeremophilane ( 5) (48 ± 2% inhibition at 50 mg/mL with IC 50 = 275 ± 5 µM); 7α- H-9(10)-ene-11,12-epoxy-8-oxoeremophilane ( 6) with 31 ± 1% inhibition at 50 mg/mL with IC 50 = 491 ± 4 µM); neopetasane ( 7) (62 ± 1% inhibition at 50 mg/mL with IC 50 = 158 ± 4 µM).
